name: flake8-print
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "flake8-print" %}
{% set version = "5.0.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "76915a2a389cc1c0879636c219eb909c38501d3a43cc8dae542081c9ba48bdf9" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
    - poetry-core
  run:
    - python >=3.7
    - flake8 >=3.0
    - pycodestyle

test:
  commands:
    - 'flake8 --version | grep flake8-print:'

about:
  home: https://github.com/jbkahn/flake8-print
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENCE
  summary: Flake8 plugin to check for print statements in python files.
  dev_url: https://github.com/jbkahn/flake8-print

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - dopplershift
